<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf023d763-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7813"><num value="7813">§ 7813.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf023d764-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7813/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such sums as are necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf023d765-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7813/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Funds appropriated under subsection (a) may not be used for the payment of the expenses or expenditures of the Board in administering a provision of an order.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf023d766-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/387/s1/a/tXII/s1214">Pub. L. 106–387, § 1(a) [title XII, § 1214]</ref>, <date date="2000-10-28">Oct. 28, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1549">114 Stat. 1549</ref>, 1549A–97.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
